105 enum lex_state_bits {
106  EXPR_BEG_bit, /* ignore newline, +/- is a sign. */
107  EXPR_END_bit, /* newline significant, +/- is an operator. */
108  EXPR_ENDARG_bit, /* ditto, and unbound braces. */
109  EXPR_ENDFN_bit, /* ditto, and unbound braces. */
110  EXPR_ARG_bit, /* newline significant, +/- is an operator. */
111  EXPR_CMDARG_bit, /* newline significant, +/- is an operator. */
112  EXPR_MID_bit, /* newline significant, +/- is an operator. */
113  EXPR_FNAME_bit, /* ignore newline, no reserved words. */
114  EXPR_DOT_bit, /* right after `.' or `::', no reserved words. */
115  EXPR_CLASS_bit, /* immediate after `class', no here document. */
116  EXPR_VALUE_bit, /* alike EXPR_BEG but label is disallowed. */
117  EXPR_LABELARG_bit, /* ignore significant, +/- is a sign. */
118  EXPR_MAX_STATE
119 };
120 /* examine combinations */
121 enum lex_state_e {
122 #define DEF_EXPR(n) EXPR_##n = (1 << EXPR_##n##_bit)
123  DEF_EXPR(BEG),
124  DEF_EXPR(END),
125  DEF_EXPR(ENDARG),
126  DEF_EXPR(ENDFN),
127  DEF_EXPR(ARG),
128  DEF_EXPR(CMDARG),
129  DEF_EXPR(MID),
130  DEF_EXPR(FNAME),
131  DEF_EXPR(DOT),
132  DEF_EXPR(CLASS),
133  DEF_EXPR(VALUE),
134  DEF_EXPR(LABELARG),
135  EXPR_BEG_ANY = (EXPR_BEG | EXPR_VALUE | EXPR_MID | EXPR_CLASS | EXPR_LABELARG),
136  EXPR_ARG_ANY = (EXPR_ARG | EXPR_CMDARG),
137  EXPR_END_ANY = (EXPR_END | EXPR_ENDARG | EXPR_ENDFN)
138 };
139 #define IS_lex_state_for(x, ls) ((x) & (ls))
140 #define IS_lex_state(ls) IS_lex_state_for(lex_state, (ls))
141

146 typedef VALUE stack_type;
147 
148 # define BITSTACK_PUSH(stack, n) ((stack) = ((stack)<<1)|((n)&1))
149 # define BITSTACK_POP(stack) ((stack) = (stack) >> 1)
150 # define BITSTACK_LEXPOP(stack) ((stack) = ((stack) >> 1) | ((stack) & 1))
151 # define BITSTACK_SET_P(stack) ((stack)&1)
152 
153 #define COND_PUSH(n) BITSTACK_PUSH(cond_stack, (n))
154 #define COND_POP() BITSTACK_POP(cond_stack)
155 #define COND_LEXPOP() BITSTACK_LEXPOP(cond_stack)
156 #define COND_P() BITSTACK_SET_P(cond_stack)
157 
158 #define CMDARG_PUSH(n) BITSTACK_PUSH(cmdarg_stack, (n))
159 #define CMDARG_POP() BITSTACK_POP(cmdarg_stack)
160 #define CMDARG_LEXPOP() BITSTACK_LEXPOP(cmdarg_stack)
161 #define CMDARG_P() BITSTACK_SET_P(cmdarg_stack)

186 static int
187 vtable_size(const struct vtable *tbl)
188 {
189  if (POINTER_P(tbl)) {
190  return tbl->pos;
191  }
192  else {
193  return 0;
194  }
195 }
196 
197 #define VTBL_DEBUG 0
198 
199 static struct vtable *
200 vtable_alloc(struct vtable *prev)
201 {
202  struct vtable *tbl = ALLOC(struct vtable);
203  tbl->pos = 0;
204  tbl->capa = 8;
205  tbl->tbl = ALLOC_N(ID, tbl->capa);
206  tbl->prev = prev;
207  if (VTBL_DEBUG) printf("vtable_alloc: %p\n", (void *)tbl);
208  return tbl;
209 }
210 
211 static void
212 vtable_free(struct vtable *tbl)
213 {
214  if (VTBL_DEBUG)printf("vtable_free: %p\n", (void *)tbl);
215  if (POINTER_P(tbl)) {
216  if (tbl->tbl) {
217  xfree(tbl->tbl);
218  }
219  xfree(tbl);
220  }
221 }
222 
223 static void
224 vtable_add(struct vtable *tbl, ID id)
225 {
226  if (!POINTER_P(tbl)) {
227  rb_bug("vtable_add: vtable is not allocated (%p)", (void *)tbl);
228  }
229  if (VTBL_DEBUG) printf("vtable_add: %p, %"PRIsVALUE"\n", (void *)tbl, rb_id2str(id));
230 
231  if (tbl->pos == tbl->capa) {
232  tbl->capa = tbl->capa * 2;
233  REALLOC_N(tbl->tbl, ID, tbl->capa);
234  }
235  tbl->tbl[tbl->pos++] = id;
236 }
237 
238 #ifndef RIPPER
239 static void
240 vtable_pop(struct vtable *tbl, int n)
241 {
242  if (tbl->pos < n) rb_bug("vtable_pop: unreachable");
243  tbl->pos -= n;
244 }
245 #endif
246 
247 static int
248 vtable_included(const struct vtable * tbl, ID id)
249 {
250  int i;
251 
252  if (POINTER_P(tbl)) {
253  for (i = 0; i < tbl->pos; i++) {
254  if (tbl->tbl[i] == id) {
255  return i+1;
256  }
257  }
258  }
259  return 0;
260 }

1090 # ifdef __GNUC__
1091 # define YYSTACK_ALLOC __builtin_alloca
1092 # elif defined __BUILTIN_VA_ARG_INCR
1093 # include <alloca.h> /* INFRINGES ON USER NAME SPACE */
1094 # elif defined _AIX
1095 # define YYSTACK_ALLOC __alloca
1096 # elif defined _MSC_VER
1097 # include <malloc.h> /* INFRINGES ON USER NAME SPACE */
1098 # define alloca _alloca
1099 # else
1100 # define YYSTACK_ALLOC alloca
1101 # if ! defined _ALLOCA_H && ! defined EXIT_SUCCESS
1102 # include <stdlib.h> /* INFRINGES ON USER NAME SPACE */
1103  /* Use EXIT_SUCCESS as a witness for stdlib.h. */
1104 # ifndef EXIT_SUCCESS
1105 # define EXIT_SUCCESS 0
1106 # endif
1107 # endif
1108 # endif
1109 # endif
1110 # endif
1111 
1112 # ifdef YYSTACK_ALLOC
1113  /* Pacify GCC's 'empty if-body' warning. */
1114 # define YYSTACK_FREE(Ptr) do { /* empty */; } while (0)
1115 # ifndef YYSTACK_ALLOC_MAXIMUM
1116  /* The OS might guarantee only one guard page at the bottom of the stack,
1117  and a page size can be as small as 4096 bytes. So we cannot safely
1118  invoke alloca (N) if N exceeds 4096. Use a slightly smaller number
1119  to allow for a few compiler-allocated temporary stack slots. */
1120 # define YYSTACK_ALLOC_MAXIMUM 4032 /* reasonable circa 2006 */
1121 # endif
1122 # else
1123 # define YYSTACK_ALLOC YYMALLOC
1124 # define YYSTACK_FREE YYFREE
1125 # ifndef YYSTACK_ALLOC_MAXIMUM
1126 # define YYSTACK_ALLOC_MAXIMUM YYSIZE_MAXIMUM
1127 # endif
1128 # if (defined __cplusplus && ! defined EXIT_SUCCESS \
1129  && ! ((defined YYMALLOC || defined malloc) \
1130  && (defined YYFREE || defined free)))
1131 # include <stdlib.h> /* INFRINGES ON USER NAME SPACE */
1132 # ifndef EXIT_SUCCESS
1133 # define EXIT_SUCCESS 0
1134 # endif
1135 # endif
1136 # ifndef YYMALLOC
1137 # define YYMALLOC malloc
1138 # if ! defined malloc && ! defined EXIT_SUCCESS
1139 void *malloc (YYSIZE_T); /* INFRINGES ON USER NAME SPACE */
1140 # endif
1141 # endif
1142 # ifndef YYFREE
1143 # define YYFREE free
1144 # if ! defined free && ! defined EXIT_SUCCESS
1145 void free (void *); /* INFRINGES ON USER NAME SPACE */
1146 # endif
1147 # endif
1148 # endif
1149 #endif /* ! defined yyoverflow || YYERROR_VERBOSE */
1150 
1151 
1152 #if (! defined yyoverflow \
1153  && (! defined __cplusplus \
1154  || (defined YYSTYPE_IS_TRIVIAL && YYSTYPE_IS_TRIVIAL)))
1155 
1156 /* A type that is properly aligned for any stack member. */
1157 union yyalloc
1158 {
1159  yytype_int16 yyss_alloc;
1160  YYSTYPE yyvs_alloc;
1161 };
1162 
1163 /* The size of the maximum gap between one aligned stack and the next. */
1164 # define YYSTACK_GAP_MAXIMUM (sizeof (union yyalloc) - 1)
1165 
1166 /* The size of an array large to enough to hold all stacks, each with
1167  N elements. */
1168 # define YYSTACK_BYTES(N) \
1169  ((N) * (sizeof (yytype_int16) + sizeof (YYSTYPE)) \
1170  + YYSTACK_GAP_MAXIMUM)
1171 
1172 # define YYCOPY_NEEDED 1
1173 
1174 /* Relocate STACK from its old location to the new one. The
1175  local variables YYSIZE and YYSTACKSIZE give the old and new number of
1176  elements in the stack, and YYPTR gives the new location of the
1177  stack. Advance YYPTR to a properly aligned location for the next
1178  stack. */
1179 # define YYSTACK_RELOCATE(Stack_alloc, Stack) \
1180  do \
1181  { \
1182  YYSIZE_T yynewbytes; \
1183  YYCOPY (&yyptr->Stack_alloc, Stack, yysize); \
1184  Stack = &yyptr->Stack_alloc; \
1185  yynewbytes = yystacksize * sizeof (*Stack) + YYSTACK_GAP_MAXIMUM; \
1186  yyptr += yynewbytes / sizeof (*yyptr); \
1187  } \
1188  while (0)
1189 
1190 #endif
1191 
1192 #if defined YYCOPY_NEEDED && YYCOPY_NEEDED
1193 /* Copy COUNT objects from SRC to DST. The source and destination do
1194  not overlap. */
1195 # ifndef YYCOPY
1196 # if defined __GNUC__ && 1 < __GNUC__
1197 # define YYCOPY(Dst, Src, Count) \
1198  __builtin_memcpy (Dst, Src, (Count) * sizeof (*(Src)))
1199 # else
1200 # define YYCOPY(Dst, Src, Count) \
1201  do \
1202  { \
1203  YYSIZE_T yyi; \
1204  for (yyi = 0; yyi < (Count); yyi++) \
1205  (Dst)[yyi] = (Src)[yyi]; \
1206  } \
1207  while (0)
1208 # endif
1209 # endif
1210 #endif /* !YYCOPY_NEEDED */

4379 #if YYERROR_VERBOSE
4380 
4381 # ifndef yystrlen
4382 # if defined __GLIBC__ && defined _STRING_H
4383 # define yystrlen strlen
4384 # else
4385 /* Return the length of YYSTR. */
4386 static YYSIZE_T
4387 yystrlen (const char *yystr)
4388 {
4389  YYSIZE_T yylen;
4390  for (yylen = 0; yystr[yylen]; yylen++)
4391  continue;
4392  return yylen;
4393 }
4394 # endif
4395 # endif
4396 
4397 # ifndef yystpcpy
4398 # if defined __GLIBC__ && defined _STRING_H && defined _GNU_SOURCE
4399 # define yystpcpy stpcpy
4400 # else
4401 /* Copy YYSRC to YYDEST, returning the address of the terminating '\0' in
4402  YYDEST. */
4403 static char *
4404 yystpcpy (char *yydest, const char *yysrc)
4405 {
4406  char *yyd = yydest;
4407  const char *yys = yysrc;
4408 
4409  while ((*yyd++ = *yys++) != '\0')
4410  continue;
4411 
4412  return yyd - 1;
4413 }
4414 # endif
4415 # endif
4416 
4417 # ifndef yytnamerr
4418 /* Copy to YYRES the contents of YYSTR after stripping away unnecessary
4419  quotes and backslashes, so that it's suitable for yyerror. The
4420  heuristic is that double-quoting is unnecessary unless the string
4421  contains an apostrophe, a comma, or backslash (other than
4422  backslash-backslash). YYSTR is taken from yytname. If YYRES is
4423  null, do not copy; instead, return the length of what the result
4424  would have been. */
4425 static YYSIZE_T
4426 yytnamerr (char *yyres, const char *yystr)
4427 {
4428  if (*yystr == '"')
4429  {
4430  YYSIZE_T yyn = 0;
4431  char const *yyp = yystr;
4432 
4433  for (;;)
4434  switch (*++yyp)
4435  {
4436  case '\'':
4437  case ',':
4438  goto do_not_strip_quotes;
4439 
4440  case '\\':
4441  if (*++yyp != '\\')
4442  goto do_not_strip_quotes;
4443  /* Fall through. */
4444  default:
4445  if (yyres)
4446  yyres[yyn] = *yyp;
4447  yyn++;
4448  break;
4449 
4450  case '"':
4451  if (yyres)
4452  yyres[yyn] = '\0';
4453  return yyn;
4454  }
4455  do_not_strip_quotes: ;
4456  }
4457 
4458  if (! yyres)
4459  return yystrlen (yystr);
4460 
4461  return yystpcpy (yyres, yystr) - yyres;
4462 }
4463 # endif
4464 
4465 /* Copy into *YYMSG, which is of size *YYMSG_ALLOC, an error message
4466  about the unexpected token YYTOKEN for the state stack whose top is
4467  YYSSP.
4468 
4469  Return 0 if *YYMSG was successfully written. Return 1 if *YYMSG is
4470  not large enough to hold the message. In that case, also set
4471  *YYMSG_ALLOC to the required number of bytes. Return 2 if the
4472  required number of bytes is too large to store. */
4473 static int
4474 yysyntax_error (YYSIZE_T *yymsg_alloc, char **yymsg,
4475  yytype_int16 *yyssp, int yytoken)
4476 {
4477  YYSIZE_T yysize0 = yytnamerr (YY_NULLPTR, yytname[yytoken]);
4478  YYSIZE_T yysize = yysize0;
4479  enum { YYERROR_VERBOSE_ARGS_MAXIMUM = 5 };
4480  /* Internationalized format string. */
4481  const char *yyformat = YY_NULLPTR;
4482  /* Arguments of yyformat. */
4483  char const *yyarg[YYERROR_VERBOSE_ARGS_MAXIMUM];
4484  /* Number of reported tokens (one for the "unexpected", one per
4485  "expected"). */
4486  int yycount = 0;
4487 
4488  /* There are many possibilities here to consider:
4489  - If this state is a consistent state with a default action, then
4490  the only way this function was invoked is if the default action
4491  is an error action. In that case, don't check for expected
4492  tokens because there are none.
4493  - The only way there can be no lookahead present (in yychar) is if
4494  this state is a consistent state with a default action. Thus,
4495  detecting the absence of a lookahead is sufficient to determine
4496  that there is no unexpected or expected token to report. In that
4497  case, just report a simple "syntax error".
4498  - Don't assume there isn't a lookahead just because this state is a
4499  consistent state with a default action. There might have been a
4500  previous inconsistent state, consistent state with a non-default
4501  action, or user semantic action that manipulated yychar.
4502  - Of course, the expected token list depends on states to have
4503  correct lookahead information, and it depends on the parser not
4504  to perform extra reductions after fetching a lookahead from the
4505  scanner and before detecting a syntax error. Thus, state merging
4506  (from LALR or IELR) and default reductions corrupt the expected
4507  token list. However, the list is correct for canonical LR with
4508  one exception: it will still contain any token that will not be
4509  accepted due to an error action in a later state.
4510  */
4511  if (yytoken != YYEMPTY)
4512  {
4513  int yyn = yypact[*yyssp];
4514  yyarg[yycount++] = yytname[yytoken];
4515  if (!yypact_value_is_default (yyn))
4516  {
4517  /* Start YYX at -YYN if negative to avoid negative indexes in
4518  YYCHECK. In other words, skip the first -YYN actions for
4519  this state because they are default actions. */
4520  int yyxbegin = yyn < 0 ? -yyn : 0;
4521  /* Stay within bounds of both yycheck and yytname. */
4522  int yychecklim = YYLAST - yyn + 1;
4523  int yyxend = yychecklim < YYNTOKENS ? yychecklim : YYNTOKENS;
4524  int yyx;
4525 
4526  for (yyx = yyxbegin; yyx < yyxend; ++yyx)
4527  if (yycheck[yyx + yyn] == yyx && yyx != YYTERROR
4528  && !yytable_value_is_error (yytable[yyx + yyn]))
4529  {
4530  if (yycount == YYERROR_VERBOSE_ARGS_MAXIMUM)
4531  {
4532  yycount = 1;
4533  yysize = yysize0;
4534  break;
4535  }
4536  yyarg[yycount++] = yytname[yyx];
4537  {
4538  YYSIZE_T yysize1 = yysize + yytnamerr (YY_NULLPTR, yytname[yyx]);
4539  if (! (yysize <= yysize1
4540  && yysize1 <= YYSTACK_ALLOC_MAXIMUM))
4541  return 2;
4542  yysize = yysize1;
4543  }
4544  }
4545  }
4546  }
4547 
4548  switch (yycount)
4549  {
4550 # define YYCASE_(N, S) \
4551  case N: \
4552  yyformat = S; \
4553  break
4554  YYCASE_(0, YY_("syntax error"));
4555  YYCASE_(1, YY_("syntax error, unexpected %s"));
4556  YYCASE_(2, YY_("syntax error, unexpected %s, expecting %s"));
4557  YYCASE_(3, YY_("syntax error, unexpected %s, expecting %s or %s"));
4558  YYCASE_(4, YY_("syntax error, unexpected %s, expecting %s or %s or %s"));
4559  YYCASE_(5, YY_("syntax error, unexpected %s, expecting %s or %s or %s or %s"));
4560 # undef YYCASE_
4561  }
4562 
4563  {
4564  YYSIZE_T yysize1 = yysize + yystrlen (yyformat);
4565  if (! (yysize <= yysize1 && yysize1 <= YYSTACK_ALLOC_MAXIMUM))
4566  return 2;
4567  yysize = yysize1;
4568  }
4569 
4570  if (*yymsg_alloc < yysize)
4571  {
4572  *yymsg_alloc = 2 * yysize;
4573  if (! (yysize <= *yymsg_alloc
4574  && *yymsg_alloc <= YYSTACK_ALLOC_MAXIMUM))
4575  *yymsg_alloc = YYSTACK_ALLOC_MAXIMUM;
4576  return 1;
4577  }
4578 
4579  /* Avoid sprintf, as that infringes on the user's name space.
4580  Don't have undefined behavior even if the translation
4581  produced a string with the wrong number of "%s"s. */
4582  {
4583  char *yyp = *yymsg;
4584  int yyi = 0;
4585  while ((*yyp = *yyformat) != '\0')
4586  if (*yyp == '%' && yyformat[1] == 's' && yyi < yycount)
4587  {
4588  yyp += yytnamerr (yyp, yyarg[yyi++]);
4589  yyformat += 2;
4590  }
4591  else
4592  {
4593  yyp++;
4594  yyformat++;
4595  }
4596  }
4597  return 0;
4598 }
4599 #endif /* YYERROR_VERBOSE */

4601 /*-----------------------------------------------.
4602 | Release the memory associated to this symbol. |
4603 `-----------------------------------------------*/
4604 
4605 static void
4606 yydestruct (const char *yymsg, int yytype, YYSTYPE *yyvaluep, struct parser_params *parser)
4607 {
4608  YYUSE (yyvaluep);
4609  YYUSE (parser);
4610  if (!yymsg)
4611  yymsg = "Deleting";

10923 /* We remove any previous definition of `SIGN_EXTEND_CHAR',
10924  since ours (we hope) works properly with all combinations of
10925  machines, compilers, `char' and `unsigned char' argument types.
10926  (Per Bothner suggested the basic approach.) */
10927 #undef SIGN_EXTEND_CHAR
10928 #if __STDC__
10929 # define SIGN_EXTEND_CHAR(c) ((signed char)(c))
10930 #else /* not __STDC__ */
10931 /* As in Harbison and Steele. */
10932 # define SIGN_EXTEND_CHAR(c) ((((unsigned char)(c)) ^ 128) - 128)
10933 #endif
10934 
10935 #define parser_encoding_name() (current_enc->name)
10936 #define parser_mbclen() mbclen((lex_p-1),lex_pend,current_enc)
10937 #define parser_precise_mbclen() rb_enc_precise_mbclen((lex_p-1),lex_pend,current_enc)
10938 #define is_identchar(p,e,enc) (rb_enc_isalnum((unsigned char)(*(p)),(enc)) || (*(p)) == '_' || !ISASCII(*(p)))
10939 #define parser_is_identchar() (!parser->eofp && is_identchar((lex_p-1),lex_pend,current_enc))
10940 
10941 #define parser_isascii() ISASCII(*(lex_p-1))

10943 #ifndef RIPPER
10944 static int
10945 token_info_get_column(struct parser_params *parser, const char *token)
10946 {
10947  int column = 1;
10948  const char *p, *pend = lex_p - strlen(token);
10949  for (p = lex_pbeg; p < pend; p++) {
10950  if (*p == '\t') {
10951  column = (((column - 1) / 8) + 1) * 8;
10952  }
10953  column++;
10954  }
10955  return column;
10956 }
10957 
10958 static int
10959 token_info_has_nonspaces(struct parser_params *parser, const char *token)
10960 {
10961  const char *p, *pend = lex_p - strlen(token);
10962  for (p = lex_pbeg; p < pend; p++) {
10963  if (*p != ' ' && *p != '\t') {
10964  return 1;
10965  }
10966  }
10967  return 0;
10968 }
10969 
10970 #undef token_info_push
10971 static void
10972 token_info_push(struct parser_params *parser, const char *token)
10973 {
10974  token_info *ptinfo;
10975 
10976  if (!parser->parser_token_info_enabled) return;
10977  ptinfo = ALLOC(token_info);
10978  ptinfo->token = token;
10979  ptinfo->linenum = ruby_sourceline;
10980  ptinfo->column = token_info_get_column(parser, token);
10981  ptinfo->nonspc = token_info_has_nonspaces(parser, token);
10982  ptinfo->next = parser->parser_token_info;
10983 
10984  parser->parser_token_info = ptinfo;
10985 }
10986 
10987 #undef token_info_pop
10988 static void
10989 token_info_pop(struct parser_params *parser, const char *token)
10990 {
10991  int linenum;
10992  token_info *ptinfo = parser->parser_token_info;
10993 
10994  if (!ptinfo) return;
10995  parser->parser_token_info = ptinfo->next;
10996  if (token_info_get_column(parser, token) == ptinfo->column) { /* OK */
10997  goto finish;
10998  }
10999  linenum = ruby_sourceline;
11000  if (linenum == ptinfo->linenum) { /* SKIP */
11001  goto finish;
11002  }
11003  if (token_info_has_nonspaces(parser, token) || ptinfo->nonspc) { /* SKIP */
11004  goto finish;
11005  }
11006  if (parser->parser_token_info_enabled) {
11007  rb_compile_warn(ruby_sourcefile, linenum,
11008  "mismatched indentations at '%s' with '%s' at %d",
11009  token, ptinfo->token, ptinfo->linenum);
11010  }
11011 
11012  finish:
11013  xfree(ptinfo);
11014 }
11015 #endif /* RIPPER */
11016 
11017 static int
11018 parser_yyerror(struct parser_params *parser, const char *msg)
11019 {
11020 #ifndef RIPPER
11021  const int max_line_margin = 30;
11022  const char *p, *pe;
11023  char *buf;
11024  long len;
11025  int i;
11026 
11027  compile_error(PARSER_ARG "%s", msg);
11028  p = lex_p;
11029  while (lex_pbeg <= p) {
11030  if (*p == '\n') break;
11031  p--;
11032  }
11033  p++;
11034 
11035  pe = lex_p;
11036  while (pe < lex_pend) {
11037  if (*pe == '\n') break;
11038  pe++;
11039  }
11040 
11041  len = pe - p;
11042  if (len > 4) {
11043  char *p2;
11044  const char *pre = "", *post = "";
11045 
11046  if (len > max_line_margin * 2 + 10) {
11047  if (lex_p - p > max_line_margin) {
11048  p = rb_enc_prev_char(p, lex_p - max_line_margin, pe, rb_enc_get(lex_lastline));
11049  pre = "...";
11050  }
11051  if (pe - lex_p > max_line_margin) {
11052  pe = rb_enc_prev_char(lex_p, lex_p + max_line_margin, pe, rb_enc_get(lex_lastline));
11053  post = "...";
11054  }
11055  len = pe - p;
11056  }
11057  buf = ALLOCA_N(char, len+2);
11058  MEMCPY(buf, p, char, len);
11059  buf[len] = '\0';
11060  rb_compile_error_with_enc(NULL, 0, (void *)current_enc, "%s%s%s", pre, buf, post);
11061 
11062  i = (int)(lex_p - p);
11063  p2 = buf; pe = buf + len;
11064 
11065  while (p2 < pe) {
11066  if (*p2 != '\t') *p2 = ' ';
11067  p2++;
11068  }
11069  buf[i] = '^';
11070  buf[i+1] = '\0';
11071  rb_compile_error_append("%s%s", pre, buf);
11072  }
11073 #else
11074  dispatch1(parse_error, STR_NEW2(msg));
11075  ripper_error();
11076 #endif /* !RIPPER */
11077  return 0;
11078 }

11082 #ifndef RIPPER
11083 static VALUE
11084 debug_lines(VALUE fname)
11085 {
11086  ID script_lines;
11087  CONST_ID(script_lines, "SCRIPT_LINES__");
11088  if (rb_const_defined_at(rb_cObject, script_lines)) {
11089  VALUE hash = rb_const_get_at(rb_cObject, script_lines);
11090  if (RB_TYPE_P(hash, T_HASH)) {
11091  VALUE lines = rb_ary_new();
11092  rb_hash_aset(hash, fname, lines);
11093  return lines;
11094  }
11095  }
11096  return 0;
11097 }

11099 static VALUE
11100 coverage(VALUE fname, int n)
11101 {
11102  VALUE coverages = rb_get_coverages();
11103  if (RTEST(coverages) && RBASIC(coverages)->klass == 0) {
11104  VALUE lines = rb_ary_tmp_new_fill(n);
11105  rb_hash_aset(coverages, fname, lines);
11106  return lines;
11107  }
11108  return 0;
11109 }

11117 static VALUE
11118 yycompile0(VALUE arg)
11119 {
11120  int n;
11121  NODE *tree;
11122  struct parser_params *parser = (struct parser_params *)arg;
11123 
11124  if (!compile_for_eval && rb_safe_level() == 0) {
11125  ruby_debug_lines = debug_lines(ruby_sourcefile_string);
11126  if (ruby_debug_lines && ruby_sourceline > 0) {
11127  VALUE str = STR_NEW0();
11128  n = ruby_sourceline;
11129  do {
11130  rb_ary_push(ruby_debug_lines, str);
11131  } while (--n);
11132  }
11133 
11134  if (!e_option_supplied(parser)) {
11135  ruby_coverage = coverage(ruby_sourcefile_string, ruby_sourceline);
11136  }
11137  }
11138  parser->last_cr_line = ruby_sourceline - 1;
11139 
11140  parser_prepare(parser);
11141  deferred_nodes = 0;
11142 #ifndef RIPPER
11143  parser->parser_token_info_enabled = !compile_for_eval && RTEST(ruby_verbose);
11144 #endif
11145 #ifndef RIPPER
11146  if (RUBY_DTRACE_PARSE_BEGIN_ENABLED()) {
11147  RUBY_DTRACE_PARSE_BEGIN(parser->parser_ruby_sourcefile,
11148  parser->parser_ruby_sourceline);
11149  }
11150 #endif
11151  n = yyparse((void*)parser);
11152 #ifndef RIPPER
11153  if (RUBY_DTRACE_PARSE_END_ENABLED()) {
11154  RUBY_DTRACE_PARSE_END(parser->parser_ruby_sourcefile,
11155  parser->parser_ruby_sourceline);
11156  }
11157 #endif
11158  ruby_debug_lines = 0;
11159  ruby_coverage = 0;
11160  compile_for_eval = 0;
11161 
11162  lex_strterm = 0;
11163  lex_p = lex_pbeg = lex_pend = 0;
11164  lex_lastline = lex_nextline = 0;
11165  if (parser->nerr) {
11166  return 0;
11167  }
11168  tree = ruby_eval_tree;
11169  if (!tree) {
11170  tree = NEW_NIL();
11171  }
11172  else if (ruby_eval_tree_begin) {
11173  tree->nd_body = NEW_PRELUDE(ruby_eval_tree_begin, tree->nd_body);
11174  }
11175  return (VALUE)tree;
11176 }

11181  ruby_sourcefile_string = rb_str_new_frozen(fname);
11182  ruby_sourcefile = RSTRING_PTR(fname);
11183  ruby_sourceline = line - 1;
11184  return (NODE *)rb_suppress_tracing(yycompile0, (VALUE)parser);
11185 }

11188 static rb_encoding *
11189 must_be_ascii_compatible(VALUE s)
11190 {

11192  if (!rb_enc_asciicompat(enc)) {
11193  rb_raise(rb_eArgError, "invalid source encoding");

11198 static VALUE
11199 lex_get_str(struct parser_params *parser, VALUE s)
11200 {
11201  char *beg, *end, *start;
11202  long len;
11203 
11204  beg = RSTRING_PTR(s);
11205  len = RSTRING_LEN(s);
11206  start = beg;
11207  if (lex_gets_ptr) {
11208  if (len == lex_gets_ptr) return Qnil;
11209  beg += lex_gets_ptr;
11210  len -= lex_gets_ptr;
11211  }
11212  end = memchr(beg, '\n', len);
11213  if (end) len = ++end - beg;
11214  lex_gets_ptr += len;
11215  return rb_str_subseq(s, beg - start, len);
11216 }
11217 
11218 static VALUE
11219 lex_getline(struct parser_params *parser)
11220 {
11221  VALUE line = (*parser->parser_lex_gets)(parser, parser->parser_lex_input);
11222  if (NIL_P(line)) return line;
11223  must_be_ascii_compatible(line);
11224 #ifndef RIPPER
11225  if (ruby_debug_lines) {
11226  rb_enc_associate(line, current_enc);
11227  rb_ary_push(ruby_debug_lines, line);
11228  }
11229  if (ruby_coverage) {
11230  rb_ary_push(ruby_coverage, Qnil);
11231  }
11232 #endif
11233  return line;
11234 }

11331 #define STR_FUNC_ESCAPE 0x01
11332 #define STR_FUNC_EXPAND 0x02
11333 #define STR_FUNC_REGEXP 0x04
11334 #define STR_FUNC_QWORDS 0x08
11335 #define STR_FUNC_SYMBOL 0x10
11336 #define STR_FUNC_INDENT 0x20
11337 #define STR_FUNC_LABEL 0x40
11338 
11339 enum string_type {
11340  str_squote = (0),
11341  str_dquote = (STR_FUNC_EXPAND),
11342  str_xquote = (STR_FUNC_EXPAND),
11343  str_regexp = (STR_FUNC_REGEXP|STR_FUNC_ESCAPE|STR_FUNC_EXPAND),
11344  str_sword = (STR_FUNC_QWORDS),
11345  str_dword = (STR_FUNC_QWORDS|STR_FUNC_EXPAND),
11346  str_ssym = (STR_FUNC_SYMBOL),
11347  str_dsym = (STR_FUNC_SYMBOL|STR_FUNC_EXPAND)
11348 };

11350 static VALUE
11351 parser_str_new(const char *p, long n, rb_encoding *enc, int func, rb_encoding *enc0)
11352 {
11353  VALUE str;
11354 
11355  str = rb_enc_str_new(p, n, enc);
11356  if (!(func & STR_FUNC_REGEXP) && rb_enc_asciicompat(enc)) {
11357  if (rb_enc_str_coderange(str) == ENC_CODERANGE_7BIT) {
11358  }
11359  else if (enc0 == rb_usascii_encoding() && enc != rb_utf8_encoding()) {
11360  rb_enc_associate(str, rb_ascii8bit_encoding());
11361  }
11362  }
11363 
11364  return str;
11365 }

11367 #define lex_goto_eol(parser) ((parser)->parser_lex_p = (parser)->parser_lex_pend)
11368 #define lex_eol_p() (lex_p >= lex_pend)
11369 #define peek(c) peek_n((c), 0)
11370 #define peek_n(c,n) (lex_p+(n) < lex_pend && (c) == (unsigned char)lex_p[n])
11371 #define peekc() peekc_n(0)
11372 #define peekc_n(n) (lex_p+(n) < lex_pend ? (unsigned char)lex_p[n] : -1)
11373 
11374 static inline int
11375 parser_nextc(struct parser_params *parser)
11376 {
11377  int c;
11378 
11379  if (lex_p == lex_pend) {
11380  VALUE v = lex_nextline;
11381  lex_nextline = 0;
11382  if (!v) {
11383  if (parser->eofp)
11384  return -1;
11385 
11386  if (!lex_input || NIL_P(v = lex_getline(parser))) {
11387  parser->eofp = Qtrue;
11388  lex_goto_eol(parser);
11389  return -1;
11390  }
11391  }
11392  {
11393 #ifdef RIPPER
11394  if (parser->tokp < lex_pend) {
11395  if (NIL_P(parser->delayed)) {
11396  parser->delayed = rb_str_buf_new(1024);
11397  rb_enc_associate(parser->delayed, current_enc);
11398  rb_str_buf_cat(parser->delayed,
11399  parser->tokp, lex_pend - parser->tokp);
11400  parser->delayed_line = ruby_sourceline;
11401  parser->delayed_col = (int)(parser->tokp - lex_pbeg);
11402  }
11403  else {
11404  rb_str_buf_cat(parser->delayed,
11405  parser->tokp, lex_pend - parser->tokp);
11406  }
11407  }
11408 #endif
11409  if (heredoc_end > 0) {
11410  ruby_sourceline = heredoc_end;
11411  heredoc_end = 0;
11412  }
11413  ruby_sourceline++;
11414  parser->line_count++;
11415  lex_pbeg = lex_p = RSTRING_PTR(v);
11416  lex_pend = lex_p + RSTRING_LEN(v);
11417  ripper_flush(parser);
11418  lex_lastline = v;
11419  }
11420  }
11421  c = (unsigned char)*lex_p++;
11422  if (c == '\r') {
11423  if (peek('\n')) {
11424  lex_p++;
11425  c = '\n';
11426  }
11427  else if (ruby_sourceline > parser->last_cr_line) {
11428  parser->last_cr_line = ruby_sourceline;
11429  rb_compile_warn(ruby_sourcefile, ruby_sourceline, "encountered \\r in middle of line, treated as a mere space");
11430  }
11431  }
11432 
11433  return c;
11434 }
11435 
11436 static void
11437 parser_pushback(struct parser_params *parser, int c)
11438 {
11439  if (c == -1) return;
11440  lex_p--;
11441  if (lex_p > lex_pbeg && lex_p[0] == '\n' && lex_p[-1] == '\r') {
11442  lex_p--;
11443  }
11444 }
11445 
11446 #define was_bol() (lex_p == lex_pbeg + 1)
11447 
11448 #define tokfix() (tokenbuf[tokidx]='\0')
11449 #define tok() tokenbuf
11450 #define toklen() tokidx
11451 #define toklast() (tokidx>0?tokenbuf[tokidx-1]:0)
11452 
11453 static char*
11454 parser_newtok(struct parser_params *parser)
11455 {
11456  tokidx = 0;
11457  tokline = ruby_sourceline;
11458  if (!tokenbuf) {
11459  toksiz = 60;
11460  tokenbuf = ALLOC_N(char, 60);
11461  }
11462  if (toksiz > 4096) {
11463  toksiz = 60;
11464  REALLOC_N(tokenbuf, char, 60);
11465  }
11466  return tokenbuf;
11467 }
11468 
11469 static char *
11470 parser_tokspace(struct parser_params *parser, int n)
11471 {
11472  tokidx += n;
11473 
11474  if (tokidx >= toksiz) {
11475  do {toksiz *= 2;} while (toksiz < tokidx);
11476  REALLOC_N(tokenbuf, char, toksiz);
11477  }
11478  return &tokenbuf[tokidx-n];
11479 }
11480 
11481 static void
11482 parser_tokadd(struct parser_params *parser, int c)
11483 {
11484  tokenbuf[tokidx++] = (char)c;
11485  if (tokidx >= toksiz) {
11486  toksiz *= 2;
11487  REALLOC_N(tokenbuf, char, toksiz);
11488  }
11489 }
11490 
11491 static int
11492 parser_tok_hex(struct parser_params *parser, size_t *numlen)
11493 {
11494  int c;
11495 
11496  c = scan_hex(lex_p, 2, numlen);
11497  if (!*numlen) {
11498  yyerror("invalid hex escape");
11499  return 0;
11500  }
11501  lex_p += *numlen;
11502  return c;
11503 }
11504 
11505 #define tokcopy(n) memcpy(tokspace(n), lex_p - (n), (n))
11506 
11507 /* return value is for ?\u3042 */
11508 static int
11509 parser_tokadd_utf8(struct parser_params *parser, rb_encoding **encp,
11510  int string_literal, int symbol_literal, int regexp_literal)
11511 {
11512  /*
11513  * If string_literal is true, then we allow multiple codepoints
11514  * in \u{}, and add the codepoints to the current token.
11515  * Otherwise we're parsing a character literal and return a single
11516  * codepoint without adding it
11517  */
11518 
11519  int codepoint;
11520  size_t numlen;
11521 
11522  if (regexp_literal) { tokadd('\\'); tokadd('u'); }
11523 
11524  if (peek('{')) { /* handle \u{...} form */
11525  do {
11526  if (regexp_literal) { tokadd(*lex_p); }
11527  nextc();
11528  codepoint = scan_hex(lex_p, 6, &numlen);
11529  if (numlen == 0) {
11530  yyerror("invalid Unicode escape");
11531  return 0;
11532  }
11533  if (codepoint > 0x10ffff) {
11534  yyerror("invalid Unicode codepoint (too large)");
11535  return 0;
11536  }
11537  lex_p += numlen;
11538  if (regexp_literal) {
11539  tokcopy((int)numlen);
11540  }
11541  else if (codepoint >= 0x80) {
11542  *encp = rb_utf8_encoding();
11543  if (string_literal) tokaddmbc(codepoint, *encp);
11544  }
11545  else if (string_literal) {
11546  tokadd(codepoint);
11547  }
11548  } while (string_literal && (peek(' ') || peek('\t')));
11549 
11550  if (!peek('}')) {
11551  yyerror("unterminated Unicode escape");
11552  return 0;
11553  }
11554 
11555  if (regexp_literal) { tokadd('}'); }
11556  nextc();
11557  }
11558  else { /* handle \uxxxx form */
11559  codepoint = scan_hex(lex_p, 4, &numlen);
11560  if (numlen < 4) {
11561  yyerror("invalid Unicode escape");
11562  return 0;
11563  }
11564  lex_p += 4;
11565  if (regexp_literal) {
11566  tokcopy(4);
11567  }
11568  else if (codepoint >= 0x80) {
11569  *encp = rb_utf8_encoding();
11570  if (string_literal) tokaddmbc(codepoint, *encp);
11571  }
11572  else if (string_literal) {
11573  tokadd(codepoint);
11574  }
11575  }
11576 
11577  return codepoint;
11578 }
11579 
11580 #define ESCAPE_CONTROL 1
11581 #define ESCAPE_META 2
11582 
11583 static int
11584 parser_read_escape(struct parser_params *parser, int flags,
11585  rb_encoding **encp)
11586 {
11587  int c;
11588  size_t numlen;
11589 
11590  switch (c = nextc()) {
11591  case '\\': /* Backslash */
11592  return c;
11593 
11594  case 'n': /* newline */
11595  return '\n';
11596 
11597  case 't': /* horizontal tab */
11598  return '\t';
11599 
11600  case 'r': /* carriage-return */
11601  return '\r';
11602 
11603  case 'f': /* form-feed */
11604  return '\f';
11605 
11606  case 'v': /* vertical tab */
11607  return '\13';
11608 
11609  case 'a': /* alarm(bell) */
11610  return '\007';
11611 
11612  case 'e': /* escape */
11613  return 033;
11614 
11615  case '0': case '1': case '2': case '3': /* octal constant */
11616  case '4': case '5': case '6': case '7':
11617  pushback(c);
11618  c = scan_oct(lex_p, 3, &numlen);
11619  lex_p += numlen;
11620  return c;
11621 
11622  case 'x': /* hex constant */
11623  c = tok_hex(&numlen);
11624  if (numlen == 0) return 0;
11625  return c;
11626 
11627  case 'b': /* backspace */
11628  return '\010';
11629 
11630  case 's': /* space */
11631  return ' ';
11632 
11633  case 'M':
11634  if (flags & ESCAPE_META) goto eof;
11635  if ((c = nextc()) != '-') {
11636  pushback(c);
11637  goto eof;
11638  }
11639  if ((c = nextc()) == '\\') {
11640  if (peek('u')) goto eof;
11641  return read_escape(flags|ESCAPE_META, encp) | 0x80;
11642  }
11643  else if (c == -1 || !ISASCII(c)) goto eof;
11644  else {
11645  return ((c & 0xff) | 0x80);
11646  }
11647 
11648  case 'C':
11649  if ((c = nextc()) != '-') {
11650  pushback(c);
11651  goto eof;
11652  }
11653  case 'c':
11654  if (flags & ESCAPE_CONTROL) goto eof;
11655  if ((c = nextc())== '\\') {
11656  if (peek('u')) goto eof;
11657  c = read_escape(flags|ESCAPE_CONTROL, encp);
11658  }
11659  else if (c == '?')
11660  return 0177;
11661  else if (c == -1 || !ISASCII(c)) goto eof;
11662  return c & 0x9f;
11663 
11664  eof:
11665  case -1:
11666  yyerror("Invalid escape character syntax");
11667  return '\0';
11668 
11669  default:
11670  return c;
11671  }
11672 }
11673 
11674 static void
11675 parser_tokaddmbc(struct parser_params *parser, int c, rb_encoding *enc)
11676 {
11677  int len = rb_enc_codelen(c, enc);
11678  rb_enc_mbcput(c, tokspace(len), enc);
11679 }
11680 
11681 static int
11682 parser_tokadd_escape(struct parser_params *parser, rb_encoding **encp)
11683 {
11684  int c;
11685  int flags = 0;
11686  size_t numlen;
11687 
11688  first:
11689  switch (c = nextc()) {
11690  case '\n':
11691  return 0; /* just ignore */
11692 
11693  case '0': case '1': case '2': case '3': /* octal constant */
11694  case '4': case '5': case '6': case '7':
11695  {
11696  ruby_scan_oct(--lex_p, 3, &numlen);
11697  if (numlen == 0) goto eof;
11698  lex_p += numlen;
11699  tokcopy((int)numlen + 1);
11700  }
11701  return 0;
11702 
11703  case 'x': /* hex constant */
11704  {
11705  tok_hex(&numlen);
11706  if (numlen == 0) return -1;
11707  tokcopy((int)numlen + 2);
11708  }
11709  return 0;
11710 
11711  case 'M':
11712  if (flags & ESCAPE_META) goto eof;
11713  if ((c = nextc()) != '-') {
11714  pushback(c);
11715  goto eof;
11716  }
11717  tokcopy(3);
11718  flags |= ESCAPE_META;
11719  goto escaped;
11720 
11721  case 'C':
11722  if (flags & ESCAPE_CONTROL) goto eof;
11723  if ((c = nextc()) != '-') {
11724  pushback(c);
11725  goto eof;
11726  }
11727  tokcopy(3);
11728  goto escaped;
11729 
11730  case 'c':
11731  if (flags & ESCAPE_CONTROL) goto eof;
11732  tokcopy(2);
11733  flags |= ESCAPE_CONTROL;
11734  escaped:
11735  if ((c = nextc()) == '\\') {
11736  goto first;
11737  }
11738  else if (c == -1) goto eof;
11739  tokadd(c);
11740  return 0;
11741 
11742  eof:
11743  case -1:
11744  yyerror("Invalid escape character syntax");
11745  return -1;
11746 
11747  default:
11748  tokadd('\\');
11749  tokadd(c);
11750  }
11751  return 0;
11752 }
11753 
11754 static int
11755 parser_regx_options(struct parser_params *parser)
11756 {
11757  int kcode = 0;
11758  int kopt = 0;
11759  int options = 0;
11760  int c, opt, kc;
11761 
11762  newtok();
11763  while (c = nextc(), ISALPHA(c)) {
11764  if (c == 'o') {
11765  options |= RE_OPTION_ONCE;
11766  }
11767  else if (rb_char_to_option_kcode(c, &opt, &kc)) {
11768  if (kc >= 0) {
11769  if (kc != rb_ascii8bit_encindex()) kcode = c;
11770  kopt = opt;
11771  }
11772  else {
11773  options |= opt;
11774  }
11775  }
11776  else {
11777  tokadd(c);
11778  }
11779  }
11780  options |= kopt;
11781  pushback(c);
11782  if (toklen()) {
11783  tokfix();
11784  compile_error(PARSER_ARG "unknown regexp option%s - %s",
11785  toklen() > 1 ? "s" : "", tok());
11786  }
11787  return options | RE_OPTION_ENCODING(kcode);
11788 }

11791 dispose_string(VALUE str)
11792 {
11793  rb_str_free(str);
11794  rb_gc_force_recycle(str);
11795 }

11797 static int
11798 parser_tokadd_mbchar(struct parser_params *parser, int c)
11799 {
11800  int len = parser_precise_mbclen();
11801  if (!MBCLEN_CHARFOUND_P(len)) {
11802  compile_error(PARSER_ARG "invalid multibyte char (%s)", parser_encoding_name());
11803  return -1;
11804  }
11805  tokadd(c);
11806  lex_p += --len;
11807  if (len > 0) tokcopy(len);
11808  return c;
11809 }
11810 
11811 #define tokadd_mbchar(c) parser_tokadd_mbchar(parser, (c))
11812 
11813 static inline int
11814 simple_re_meta(int c)
11815 {
11816  switch (c) {
11817  case '$': case '*': case '+': case '.':
11818  case '?': case '^': case '|':
11819  case ')': case ']': case '}': case '>':
11820  return TRUE;
11821  default:
11822  return FALSE;
11823  }
11824 }
11825 
11826 static int
11827 parser_tokadd_string(struct parser_params *parser,
11828  int func, int term, int paren, long *nest,
11829  rb_encoding **encp)
11830 {
11831  int c;
11832  int has_nonascii = 0;
11833  rb_encoding *enc = *encp;
11834  char *errbuf = 0;
11835  static const char mixed_msg[] = "%s mixed within %s source";
11836 
11837 #define mixed_error(enc1, enc2) if (!errbuf) { \
11838  size_t len = sizeof(mixed_msg) - 4; \
11839  len += strlen(rb_enc_name(enc1)); \
11840  len += strlen(rb_enc_name(enc2)); \
11841  errbuf = ALLOCA_N(char, len); \
11842  snprintf(errbuf, len, mixed_msg, \
11843  rb_enc_name(enc1), \
11844  rb_enc_name(enc2)); \
11845  yyerror(errbuf); \
11846  }
11847 #define mixed_escape(beg, enc1, enc2) do { \
11848  const char *pos = lex_p; \
11849  lex_p = (beg); \
11850  mixed_error((enc1), (enc2)); \
11851  lex_p = pos; \
11852  } while (0)
11853 
11854  while ((c = nextc()) != -1) {
11855  if (paren && c == paren) {
11856  ++*nest;
11857  }
11858  else if (c == term) {
11859  if (!nest || !*nest) {
11860  pushback(c);
11861  break;
11862  }
11863  --*nest;
11864  }
11865  else if ((func & STR_FUNC_EXPAND) && c == '#' && lex_p < lex_pend) {
11866  int c2 = *lex_p;
11867  if (c2 == '$' || c2 == '@' || c2 == '{') {
11868  pushback(c);
11869  break;
11870  }
11871  }
11872  else if (c == '\\') {
11873  const char *beg = lex_p - 1;
11874  c = nextc();
11875  switch (c) {
11876  case '\n':
11877  if (func & STR_FUNC_QWORDS) break;
11878  if (func & STR_FUNC_EXPAND) continue;
11879  tokadd('\\');
11880  break;
11881 
11882  case '\\':
11883  if (func & STR_FUNC_ESCAPE) tokadd(c);
11884  break;
11885 
11886  case 'u':
11887  if ((func & STR_FUNC_EXPAND) == 0) {
11888  tokadd('\\');
11889  break;
11890  }
11891  parser_tokadd_utf8(parser, &enc, 1,
11892  func & STR_FUNC_SYMBOL,
11893  func & STR_FUNC_REGEXP);
11894  if (has_nonascii && enc != *encp) {
11895  mixed_escape(beg, enc, *encp);
11896  }
11897  continue;
11898 
11899  default:
11900  if (c == -1) return -1;
11901  if (!ISASCII(c)) {
11902  if ((func & STR_FUNC_EXPAND) == 0) tokadd('\\');
11903  goto non_ascii;
11904  }
11905  if (func & STR_FUNC_REGEXP) {
11906  if (c == term && !simple_re_meta(c)) {
11907  tokadd(c);
11908  continue;
11909  }
11910  pushback(c);
11911  if ((c = tokadd_escape(&enc)) < 0)
11912  return -1;
11913  if (has_nonascii && enc != *encp) {
11914  mixed_escape(beg, enc, *encp);
11915  }
11916  continue;
11917  }
11918  else if (func & STR_FUNC_EXPAND) {
11919  pushback(c);
11920  if (func & STR_FUNC_ESCAPE) tokadd('\\');
11921  c = read_escape(0, &enc);
11922  }
11923  else if ((func & STR_FUNC_QWORDS) && ISSPACE(c)) {
11924  /* ignore backslashed spaces in %w */
11925  }
11926  else if (c != term && !(paren && c == paren)) {
11927  tokadd('\\');
11928  pushback(c);
11929  continue;
11930  }
11931  }
11932  }
11933  else if (!parser_isascii()) {
11934  non_ascii:
11935  has_nonascii = 1;
11936  if (enc != *encp) {
11937  mixed_error(enc, *encp);
11938  continue;
11939  }
11940  if (tokadd_mbchar(c) == -1) return -1;
11941  continue;
11942  }
11943  else if ((func & STR_FUNC_QWORDS) && ISSPACE(c)) {
11944  pushback(c);
11945  break;
11946  }
11947  if (c & 0x80) {
11948  has_nonascii = 1;
11949  if (enc != *encp) {
11950  mixed_error(enc, *encp);
11951  continue;
11952  }
11953  }
11954  tokadd(c);
11955  }
11956  *encp = enc;
11957  return c;
11958 }
11959 
11960 #define NEW_STRTERM(func, term, paren) \
11961  rb_node_newnode(NODE_STRTERM, (func), (term) | ((paren) << (CHAR_BIT * 2)), 0)
11962 
11963 #ifdef RIPPER
11964 static void
11965 ripper_flush_string_content(struct parser_params *parser, rb_encoding *enc)
11966 {
11967  VALUE content = yylval.val;
11968  if (!ripper_is_node_yylval(content))
11969  content = ripper_new_yylval(0, 0, content);
11970  if (!NIL_P(parser->delayed)) {
11971  ptrdiff_t len = lex_p - parser->tokp;
11972  if (len > 0) {
11973  rb_enc_str_buf_cat(parser->delayed, parser->tokp, len, enc);
11974  }
11975  ripper_dispatch_delayed_token(parser, tSTRING_CONTENT);
11976  parser->tokp = lex_p;
11977  RNODE(content)->nd_rval = yylval.val;
11978  }
11979  ripper_dispatch_scan_event(parser, tSTRING_CONTENT);
11980  if (yylval.val != content)
11981  RNODE(content)->nd_rval = yylval.val;
11982  yylval.val = content;
11983 }

11990 RUBY_FUNC_EXPORTED const unsigned int ruby_global_name_punct_bits[(0x7e - 0x20 + 31) / 32];
11991 /* this can be shared with ripper, since it's independent from struct
11992  * parser_params. */
11993 #ifndef RIPPER
11994 #define BIT(c, idx) (((c) / 32 - 1 == idx) ? (1U << ((c) % 32)) : 0)
11995 #define SPECIAL_PUNCT(idx) ( \
11996  BIT('~', idx) | BIT('*', idx) | BIT('$', idx) | BIT('?', idx) | \
11997  BIT('!', idx) | BIT('@', idx) | BIT('/', idx) | BIT('\\', idx) | \
11998  BIT(';', idx) | BIT(',', idx) | BIT('.', idx) | BIT('=', idx) | \
11999  BIT(':', idx) | BIT('<', idx) | BIT('>', idx) | BIT('\"', idx) | \
12000  BIT('&', idx) | BIT('`', idx) | BIT('\'', idx) | BIT('+', idx) | \
12001  BIT('0', idx))
12002 const unsigned int ruby_global_name_punct_bits[] = {
12003  SPECIAL_PUNCT(0),
12004  SPECIAL_PUNCT(1),
12005  SPECIAL_PUNCT(2),
12006 };
12007 #undef BIT
12008 #undef SPECIAL_PUNCT
12009 #endif

12011 static int
12012 parser_peek_variable_name(struct parser_params *parser)
12013 {
12014  int c;
12015  const char *p = lex_p;
12016 
12017  if (p + 1 >= lex_pend) return 0;
12018  c = *p++;
12019  switch (c) {
12020  case '$':
12021  if ((c = *p) == '-') {
12022  if (++p >= lex_pend) return 0;
12023  c = *p;
12024  }
12025  else if (is_global_name_punct(c) || ISDIGIT(c)) {
12026  return tSTRING_DVAR;
12027  }
12028  break;
12029  case '@':
12030  if ((c = *p) == '@') {
12031  if (++p >= lex_pend) return 0;
12032  c = *p;
12033  }
12034  break;
12035  case '{':
12036  lex_p = p;
12037  command_start = TRUE;
12038  return tSTRING_DBEG;
12039  default:
12040  return 0;
12041  }
12042  if (!ISASCII(c) || c == '_' || ISALPHA(c))
12043  return tSTRING_DVAR;
12044  return 0;
12045 }
12046 
12047 static int
12048 parser_parse_string(struct parser_params *parser, NODE *quote)
12049 {
12050  int func = (int)quote->nd_func;
12051  int term = nd_term(quote);
12052  int paren = nd_paren(quote);
12053  int c, space = 0;
12054  rb_encoding *enc = current_enc;
12055 
12056  if (func == -1) return tSTRING_END;
12057  c = nextc();
12058  if ((func & STR_FUNC_QWORDS) && ISSPACE(c)) {
12059  do {c = nextc();} while (ISSPACE(c));
12060  space = 1;
12061  }
12062  if (c == term && !quote->nd_nest) {
12063  if (func & STR_FUNC_QWORDS) {
12064  quote->nd_func = -1;
12065  return ' ';
12066  }
12067  if (!(func & STR_FUNC_REGEXP)) return tSTRING_END;
12068  set_yylval_num(regx_options());
12069 #ifdef RIPPER
12070  ripper_dispatch_scan_event(parser, tREGEXP_END);
12071 #endif
12072  return tREGEXP_END;
12073  }
12074  if (space) {
12075  pushback(c);
12076  return ' ';
12077  }
12078  newtok();
12079  if ((func & STR_FUNC_EXPAND) && c == '#') {
12080  int t = parser_peek_variable_name(parser);
12081  if (t) return t;
12082  tokadd('#');
12083  c = nextc();
12084  }
12085  pushback(c);
12086  if (tokadd_string(func, term, paren, &quote->nd_nest,
12087  &enc) == -1) {
12088  ruby_sourceline = nd_line(quote);
12089  if (func & STR_FUNC_REGEXP) {
12090  if (parser->eofp)
12091  compile_error(PARSER_ARG "unterminated regexp meets end of file");
12092  return tREGEXP_END;
12093  }
12094  else {
12095  if (parser->eofp)
12096  compile_error(PARSER_ARG "unterminated string meets end of file");
12097  return tSTRING_END;
12098  }
12099  }
12100 
12101  tokfix();
12102  set_yylval_str(STR_NEW3(tok(), toklen(), enc, func));
12103  flush_string_content(enc);
12104 
12105  return tSTRING_CONTENT;
12106 }
12107 
12108 static int
12109 parser_heredoc_identifier(struct parser_params *parser)
12110 {
12111  int c = nextc(), term, func = 0;
12112  long len;
12113 
12114  if (c == '-') {
12115  c = nextc();
12116  func = STR_FUNC_INDENT;
12117  }
12118  switch (c) {
12119  case '\'':
12120  func |= str_squote; goto quoted;
12121  case '"':
12122  func |= str_dquote; goto quoted;
12123  case '`':
12124  func |= str_xquote;
12125  quoted:
12126  newtok();
12127  tokadd(func);
12128  term = c;
12129  while ((c = nextc()) != -1 && c != term) {
12130  if (tokadd_mbchar(c) == -1) return 0;
12131  }
12132  if (c == -1) {
12133  compile_error(PARSER_ARG "unterminated here document identifier");
12134  return 0;
12135  }
12136  break;
12137 
12138  default:
12139  if (!parser_is_identchar()) {
12140  pushback(c);
12141  if (func & STR_FUNC_INDENT) {
12142  pushback('-');
12143  }
12144  return 0;
12145  }
12146  newtok();
12147  term = '"';
12148  tokadd(func |= str_dquote);
12149  do {
12150  if (tokadd_mbchar(c) == -1) return 0;
12151  } while ((c = nextc()) != -1 && parser_is_identchar());
12152  pushback(c);
12153  break;
12154  }
12155 
12156  tokfix();
12157 #ifdef RIPPER
12158  ripper_dispatch_scan_event(parser, tHEREDOC_BEG);
12159 #endif
12160  len = lex_p - lex_pbeg;
12161  lex_goto_eol(parser);
12162  lex_strterm = rb_node_newnode(NODE_HEREDOC,
12163  STR_NEW(tok(), toklen()), /* nd_lit */
12164  len, /* nd_nth */
12165  lex_lastline); /* nd_orig */
12166  nd_set_line(lex_strterm, ruby_sourceline);
12167  ripper_flush(parser);
12168  return term == '`' ? tXSTRING_BEG : tSTRING_BEG;
12169 }
12170 
12171 static void
12172 parser_heredoc_restore(struct parser_params *parser, NODE *here)
12173 {
12174  VALUE line;
12175 
12176  lex_strterm = 0;
12177  line = here->nd_orig;
12178  lex_lastline = line;
12179  lex_pbeg = RSTRING_PTR(line);
12180  lex_pend = lex_pbeg + RSTRING_LEN(line);
12181  lex_p = lex_pbeg + here->nd_nth;
12182  heredoc_end = ruby_sourceline;
12183  ruby_sourceline = nd_line(here);
12184  dispose_string(here->nd_lit);
12185  rb_gc_force_recycle((VALUE)here);
12186  ripper_flush(parser);
12187 }
12188 
12189 static int
12190 parser_whole_match_p(struct parser_params *parser,
12191  const char *eos, long len, int indent)
12192 {
12193  const char *p = lex_pbeg;
12194  long n;
12195 
12196  if (indent) {
12197  while (*p && ISSPACE(*p)) p++;
12198  }
12199  n = lex_pend - (p + len);
12200  if (n < 0) return FALSE;
12201  if (n > 0 && p[len] != '\n') {
12202  if (p[len] != '\r') return FALSE;
12203  if (n <= 1 || p[len+1] != '\n') return FALSE;
12204  }
12205  return strncmp(eos, p, len) == 0;
12206 }
12207 
12208 #define NUM_SUFFIX_R (1<<0)
12209 #define NUM_SUFFIX_I (1<<1)
12210 #define NUM_SUFFIX_ALL 3
12211 
12212 static int
12213 parser_number_literal_suffix(struct parser_params *parser, int mask)
12214 {
12215  int c, result = 0;
12216  const char *lastp = lex_p;
12217 
12218  while ((c = nextc()) != -1) {
12219  if ((mask & NUM_SUFFIX_I) && c == 'i') {
12220  result |= (mask & NUM_SUFFIX_I);
12221  mask &= ~NUM_SUFFIX_I;
12222  /* r after i, rational of complex is disallowed */
12223  mask &= ~NUM_SUFFIX_R;
12224  continue;
12225  }
12226  if ((mask & NUM_SUFFIX_R) && c == 'r') {
12227  result |= (mask & NUM_SUFFIX_R);
12228  mask &= ~NUM_SUFFIX_R;
12229  continue;
12230  }
12231  if (!ISASCII(c) || ISALPHA(c) || c == '_') {
12232  lex_p = lastp;
12233  return 0;
12234  }
12235  pushback(c);
12236  if (c == '.') {
12237  c = peekc_n(1);
12238  if (ISDIGIT(c)) {
12239  yyerror("unexpected fraction part after numeric literal");
12240  lex_p += 2;
12241  while (parser_is_identchar()) nextc();
12242  }
12243  }
12244  break;
12245  }
12246  return result;
12247 }
12248 
12249 static int
12250 parser_set_number_literal(struct parser_params *parser, VALUE v, int type, int suffix)
12251 {
12252  if (suffix & NUM_SUFFIX_I) {
12253  v = rb_complex_raw(INT2FIX(0), v);
12254  type = tIMAGINARY;
12255  }
12256  set_yylval_literal(v);
12257  return type;
12258 }
12259 
12260 static int
12261 parser_set_integer_literal(struct parser_params *parser, VALUE v, int suffix)
12262 {
12263  int type = tINTEGER;
12264  if (suffix & NUM_SUFFIX_R) {
12265  v = rb_rational_raw1(v);
12266  type = tRATIONAL;
12267  }
12268  return set_number_literal(v, type, suffix);
12269 }

12271 #ifdef RIPPER
12272 static void
12273 ripper_dispatch_heredoc_end(struct parser_params *parser)
12274 {
12275  if (!NIL_P(parser->delayed))
12276  ripper_dispatch_delayed_token(parser, tSTRING_CONTENT);
12277  lex_goto_eol(parser);
12278  ripper_dispatch_ignored_scan_event(parser, tHEREDOC_END);
12279 }
12280 
12281 #define dispatch_heredoc_end() ripper_dispatch_heredoc_end(parser)
12282 #else
12283 #define dispatch_heredoc_end() ((void)0)
12284 #endif
12285 
12286 static int
12287 parser_here_document(struct parser_params *parser, NODE *here)
12288 {
12289  int c, func, indent = 0;
12290  const char *eos, *p, *pend;
12291  long len;
12292  VALUE str = 0;
12293  rb_encoding *enc = current_enc;
12294 
12295  eos = RSTRING_PTR(here->nd_lit);
12296  len = RSTRING_LEN(here->nd_lit) - 1;
12297  indent = (func = *eos++) & STR_FUNC_INDENT;
12298 
12299  if ((c = nextc()) == -1) {
12300  error:
12301  compile_error(PARSER_ARG "can't find string \"%s\" anywhere before EOF", eos);
12302 #ifdef RIPPER
12303  if (NIL_P(parser->delayed)) {
12304  ripper_dispatch_scan_event(parser, tSTRING_CONTENT);
12305  }
12306  else {
12307  if (str) {
12308  rb_str_append(parser->delayed, str);
12309  }
12310  else if ((len = lex_p - parser->tokp) > 0) {
12311  if (!(func & STR_FUNC_REGEXP) && rb_enc_asciicompat(enc)) {
12312  int cr = ENC_CODERANGE_UNKNOWN;
12313  rb_str_coderange_scan_restartable(parser->tokp, lex_p, enc, &cr);
12314  if (cr != ENC_CODERANGE_7BIT &&
12315  current_enc == rb_usascii_encoding() &&
12316  enc != rb_utf8_encoding()) {
12317  enc = rb_ascii8bit_encoding();
12318  }
12319  }
12320  rb_enc_str_buf_cat(parser->delayed, parser->tokp, len, enc);
12321  }
12322  ripper_dispatch_delayed_token(parser, tSTRING_CONTENT);
12323  }
12324  lex_goto_eol(parser);
12325 #endif
12326  restore:
12327  heredoc_restore(lex_strterm);
12328  return 0;
12329  }
12330  if (was_bol() && whole_match_p(eos, len, indent)) {
12331  dispatch_heredoc_end();
12332  heredoc_restore(lex_strterm);
12333  return tSTRING_END;
12334  }
12335 
12336  if (!(func & STR_FUNC_EXPAND)) {
12337  do {
12338  p = RSTRING_PTR(lex_lastline);
12339  pend = lex_pend;
12340  if (pend > p) {
12341  switch (pend[-1]) {
12342  case '\n':
12343  if (--pend == p || pend[-1] != '\r') {
12344  pend++;
12345  break;
12346  }
12347  case '\r':
12348  --pend;
12349  }
12350  }
12351  if (str)
12352  rb_str_cat(str, p, pend - p);
12353  else
12354  str = STR_NEW(p, pend - p);
12355  if (pend < lex_pend) rb_str_cat(str, "\n", 1);
12356  lex_goto_eol(parser);
12357  if (nextc() == -1) {
12358  if (str) {
12359  dispose_string(str);
12360  str = 0;
12361  }
12362  goto error;
12363  }
12364  } while (!whole_match_p(eos, len, indent));
12365  }
12366  else {
12367  /* int mb = ENC_CODERANGE_7BIT, *mbp = &mb;*/
12368  newtok();
12369  if (c == '#') {
12370  int t = parser_peek_variable_name(parser);
12371  if (t) return t;
12372  tokadd('#');
12373  c = nextc();
12374  }
12375  do {
12376  pushback(c);
12377  if ((c = tokadd_string(func, '\n', 0, NULL, &enc)) == -1) {
12378  if (parser->eofp) goto error;
12379  goto restore;
12380  }
12381  if (c != '\n') {
12382  set_yylval_str(STR_NEW3(tok(), toklen(), enc, func));
12383  flush_string_content(enc);
12384  return tSTRING_CONTENT;
12385  }
12386  tokadd(nextc());
12387  /* if (mbp && mb == ENC_CODERANGE_UNKNOWN) mbp = 0;*/
12388  if ((c = nextc()) == -1) goto error;
12389  } while (!whole_match_p(eos, len, indent));
12390  str = STR_NEW3(tok(), toklen(), enc, func);
12391  }
12392  dispatch_heredoc_end();
12393  heredoc_restore(lex_strterm);
12394  lex_strterm = NEW_STRTERM(-1, 0, 0);
12395  set_yylval_str(str);
12396  return tSTRING_CONTENT;
12397 }

12402 arg_ambiguous_gen(struct parser_params *parser, char c)

12406 #else

12412 static ID
12413 formal_argument_gen(struct parser_params *parser, ID lhs)
12414 {
12415  switch (id_type(lhs)) {
12416  case ID_LOCAL:
12417  break;
12418 #ifndef RIPPER
12419  case ID_CONST:
12420  yyerror("formal argument cannot be a constant");
12421  return 0;
12422  case ID_INSTANCE:
12423  yyerror("formal argument cannot be an instance variable");
12424  return 0;
12425  case ID_GLOBAL:
12426  yyerror("formal argument cannot be a global variable");
12427  return 0;
12428  case ID_CLASS:
12429  yyerror("formal argument cannot be a class variable");
12430  return 0;
12431 #else
12432  default:
12433  lhs = dispatch1(param_error, lhs);
12434  ripper_error();
12435  return 0;
12436 #endif
12437  }
12438  shadowing_lvar(lhs);
12439  return lhs;
12440 }

12448 /* emacsen -*- hack */
12449 static long
12450 parser_encode_length(struct parser_params *parser, const char *name, long len)
12451 {
12452  long nlen;
12453 
12454  if (len > 5 && name[nlen = len - 5] == '-') {
12455  if (rb_memcicmp(name + nlen + 1, "unix", 4) == 0)
12456  return nlen;
12457  }
12458  if (len > 4 && name[nlen = len - 4] == '-') {
12459  if (rb_memcicmp(name + nlen + 1, "dos", 3) == 0)
12460  return nlen;
12461  if (rb_memcicmp(name + nlen + 1, "mac", 3) == 0 &&
12462  !(len == 8 && rb_memcicmp(name, "utf8-mac", len) == 0))
12463  /* exclude UTF8-MAC because the encoding named "UTF8" doesn't exist in Ruby */
12464  return nlen;
12465  }
12466  return len;
12467 }
12468 
12469 static void
12470 parser_set_encode(struct parser_params *parser, const char *name)
12471 {
12472  int idx = rb_enc_find_index(name);
12473  rb_encoding *enc;
12474  VALUE excargs[3];
12475 
12476  if (idx < 0) {
12477  excargs[1] = rb_sprintf("unknown encoding name: %s", name);
12478  error:
12479  excargs[0] = rb_eArgError;
12480  excargs[2] = rb_make_backtrace();
12481  rb_ary_unshift(excargs[2], rb_sprintf("%s:%d", ruby_sourcefile, ruby_sourceline));
12482  rb_exc_raise(rb_make_exception(3, excargs));
12483  }
12484  enc = rb_enc_from_index(idx);
12485  if (!rb_enc_asciicompat(enc)) {
12486  excargs[1] = rb_sprintf("%s is not ASCII compatible", rb_enc_name(enc));
12487  goto error;
12488  }
12489  parser->enc = enc;
12490 #ifndef RIPPER
12491  if (ruby_debug_lines) {
12492  VALUE lines = ruby_debug_lines;
12493  long i, n = RARRAY_LEN(lines);
12494  for (i = 0; i < n; ++i) {
12495  rb_enc_associate_index(RARRAY_AREF(lines, i), idx);
12496  }
12497  }
12498 #endif
12499 }

12501 static int
12502 comment_at_top(struct parser_params *parser)
12503 {
12504  const char *p = lex_pbeg, *pend = lex_p - 1;
12505  if (parser->line_count != (parser->has_shebang ? 2 : 1)) return 0;
12506  while (p < pend) {
12507  if (!ISSPACE(*p)) return 0;
12508  p++;
12509  }
12510  return 1;
12511 }

12513 typedef long (*rb_magic_comment_length_t)(struct parser_params *parser, const char *name, long len);
12514 typedef void (*rb_magic_comment_setter_t)(struct parser_params *parser, const char *name, const char *val);
12515 
12516 static void
12517 magic_comment_encoding(struct parser_params *parser, const char *name, const char *val)
12518 {
12519  if (!comment_at_top(parser)) {
12520  return;
12521  }
12522  parser_set_encode(parser, val);
12523 }

12525 #ifndef RIPPER
12526 static int
12527 parser_get_bool(struct parser_params *parser, const char *name, const char *val)
12528 {
12529  switch (*val) {
12530  case 't': case 'T':
12531  if (strcasecmp(val, "true") == 0) {
12532  return TRUE;
12533  }
12534  break;
12535  case 'f': case 'F':
12536  if (strcasecmp(val, "false") == 0) {
12537  return FALSE;
12538  }
12539  break;
12540  }
12541  rb_compile_warning(ruby_sourcefile, ruby_sourceline, "invalid value for %s: %s", name, val);
12542  return -1;
12543 }

12549  if (b >= 0) parser->parser_token_info_enabled = b;
12550 }

12562 struct magic_comment {
12563  const char *name;
12564  rb_magic_comment_setter_t func;
12565  rb_magic_comment_length_t length;
12566 };
12567 
12568 static const struct magic_comment magic_comments[] = {
12569  {"coding", magic_comment_encoding, parser_encode_length},
12570  {"encoding", magic_comment_encoding, parser_encode_length},
12571 #ifndef RIPPER
12572  {"warn_indent", parser_set_token_info},
12573 # if WARN_PAST_SCOPE
12574  {"warn_past_scope", parser_set_past_scope},
12575 # endif
12576 #endif
12577 };
